        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsible Wildland Fire Recovery Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill authorizes the Department of Agriculture (USDA) to waive certain requirements for matching federal funds in fire recovery projects. Specifically, USDA may waive cost-sharing requirements for projects responding to fires resulting from management activities (e.g., controlled burns) conducted by USDA on National Forest System land.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
